post_text: Nineteen years ago on September 11, 2001, at 8:46 am Eastern time, the United States of America came under attack, as a jet filled with people crashed into the World Trade Center North Tower in New York City. At 9:03, a second jet struck the South Tower and at 9:37 the Pentagon was hit by a third plane. At 9:59 the South Tower collapsed and 8 minutes later Flight 93 crashed in a field in Pennsylvania as passengers attempted to stop the terrorists who were headed for the White House or the Capital. At 10:28 the North Tower collapsed. 2996 people died that morning and in that 2 hour time span, the world as we once knew it, changed forever. It was the first time most of us did not feel safe in our own country and had no idea what would happen next. Brave men and women gave their lives to try to save others and it took months to clear the debris. As we observe our moment of silence today, please take the time to remember the events of 9/11. Nineteen years later there are still thousands of families affected by the tragedy.

Nineteen years later there are still thousands of families affected by the tragedy.

post_text:
WIXY Spirit Showdown

Voting starts on September 14th!

There won't be cheering fans on the sidelines, in the stands, or on the course this Fall. So, instead of Football games on Fridays this year, we're going to turn the competitions over to the FANS.

It's the School Spirit Showdown, where the most passionate fan base wins! If your school turns out big for volleyball, football, tennis, band, cheer, or ANYTHING We want to know. We're looking for the most passionate boosters of their school in Central Illinois.

Every week for six weeks, we'll have match-ups between two local schools. Voting will be open from Monday through Thursday at 11:59
pm. The school that gets the most votes moves on to the next round. The school that beats them all, and is crowned champion will win

The School Spirit Showdown Travelling Trophy, and gets $1000 donated to their school!

#vgbluedevils

post_text:
The U.S. Department of Agriculture is extending the Summer Food Service Program waiver from September 1 to December 31. Our district waiver was completed this morning.

What does this mean to you? It means the Villa Grove School District is eligible to offer breakfast and lunch FREE to ALL students enrolled in Villa Grove School District #302 from September 1 to the end of the first semester!

You do not have to do anything. If your child wants to eat breakfast and/or lunch, they will be able to at no cost to you. This applies to all days, remote and in person. We will be sending out weekly lunch orders for students requesting lunches or breakfast for remote days.

Please be sure to sign up with the link sent to your email by noon each Thursday.

Update: TeacherEase does not currently support Android. If you are trying to access with an Android the app will not work. The have an app sent in for approval but are waiting. If you are having trouble you can still sign in and self certify through the web page.

Parents/Guardians will have to self-certify their students daily for those attending in-person. If you are remote learning for the day you do not need to complete the self-certification. If you do not have access to self-certify using TeacherEase, a paper version of the Wellness Screening is provided in the comments. The questions have to be answered daily and initialed by the parent or guardian. The students will show the door monitors or teacher their wellness screening sheet.

post_text:
The Illinois State Board of Education released new guidance on Thursday, July 23rd for reopening of schools. We are continuing with our plan that the Villa Grove School Board approved on Monday July 22nd. The one change will be adding a Remote Learning option for students.

We are reaching out again to gather some very valuable and critical information related to remote learning moving forward. In order for us to make an informed decision regarding student groups for Blue and Gold Days and delivery of instruction we need to gather a list of those that are choosing the remote option. We need to have your decision to pursue remote learning by Friday, August 7th at 3 pm. Once you select this option your student must remain in remote learning for the entire duration of the first quarter. After the first quarter we will reevaluate our Blended and Remote Learning options.

Thank you and once again thanks for your patience and understanding during this challenging time for all. If you have any questions please contact your building administrator.

https://forms.gle/HEA13gn1CFNnryKq8

Villa Grove CUSD #302 is moving all registration to an online format and is currently open for our 2020-2021 school year. Registration will be open in TeacherEase from Monday, July 27th through Friday, August 7th. If you do not have access to a computer or need assistance in registering online, please call the school office to schedule an appointment. I will send out a tutorial video later today. You may pay for registration fees online or make a payment in the office.

New families to our district please call the Unit Office 217.832.2261 to begin the registration process.

Information on student assignments for Blue and Gold (Monday/Wednesday or Tuesday/Thursday) Days will be sent out later. More information will be sent out later this week to help finalize this process.

post_text:
On March 16, 2020, Governor Pritizker issued an Executive Order restricting public gatherings, encouraging citizens to stay-at-home and practice social distancing in response to the Coronavirus Pandemic. As part of that order, the Governor suspended certain requirements of the Open Meeting Act in order to prevent the spread of the virus.

Therefore, the Villa Grove Board of Education monthly meeting on June 18, 2020 at 6:00 PM will not be open for in-person attendance by the public. The meeting will be broadcast live on a streaming site provided later. Community members who wish to submit public comments to the Board may do so by sending an email to BOE@vg302.org prior to the meeting.

Villa Grove Board of Education

post_text: Villa Grove CUSD #302 would like to extend its sincere condolences to the family of Barb Thomas. Barb served as the District‚Äôs Treasurer for nearly 57 years. She and her husband, Frank, were huge fans and supporters of all Blue Devil athletics. Barb always shared a smile, a funny story, and a laugh whenever she could. She will be missed terribly, and we wish her family and friends comfort during this time of grief.

On March 16, 2020, Governor Pritizker issued an Executive Order restricting public gatherings, encouraging citizens to stay-at-home and practice social distancing in response to the Coronavirus Pandemic. As part of that order, the Governor suspended certain requirements of the Open Meeting Act in order to prevent the spread of the virus.

Therefore, the Villa Grove Board of Education monthly meeting on May 18, 2020 at 6:00 PM will not be open for in-person attendance by the public. The meeting will be broadcast live on a streaming site provided later. Community members who wish to submit public comments to the Board may do so by sending an email to BOE@vg302.org prior to the meeting.

Villa Grove Board of Education

During the April Board Meeting, The School Board decided to refund sport fees for student athletes that were unable to practice or compete in any of our Spring sports.

A letter is being mailed out today with three options:

Please refund the full amount paid.

Please hold the fees and apply to student participation fees for the 2020-21 school year.

Please accept my sports fee/transportation fee as a donation to the school‚Äôs athletic program.

Some families have chosen to donate the fees back to the district to help offset the cost of coaching salaries and other expenses.

Please return the letter, indicating your preference, to the school. You may drop it off during our regular meal and/or learning packet distribution times, or you may mail it to the school.

Governor Pritzker announced that in-person learning will be suspended for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school.

We will continue to provide online and hard copy learning packets through the end of the school calendar at the end of May.

Please continue to watch for future announcements in regards to events such as prom, 8th grade promotion, and HS graduation, and other school events.

We ask that you please be patient as we work out these details. We will pass along all the information as it becomes available.
#vgbluedevils #vgstayingconnected

Villa Grove CUSD #302 is continuing to provide food for our students during our school closure.

Each week, in order to make sure we have enough meals, please complete the form for your children who attend school in our school district who would like to request meals (breakfast and lunch) during our emergency school closure. There will be no charge for these meals for any student.

The pickup date for this pre-order is Tuesday, April 14 from 10:00-12:30 in Villa Grove and 11:30-12:30 in Camargo. Please place your order by noon this Thursday, April 9.

Please reach out to school administration via phone or email if you cannot make this time frame.

Please go to the following link to place your request. If you are unable to complete the form please call the school at 217-832-2261.

https://forms.gle/gbt2hvmY38ZvVq7N9

post_text:
Hello, I sure hope everyone's healthy. Alumni weekend has been postponed until September 19th. We all agree on this date. We being the people who take care of the different activities, golf outing, dance, banquet and Nifty 50's. We considered Homecoming, which is in October, but traditionally, that week is full of activities for the kids and their dance is on Saturday night.
The reason for September 19th and 20th, it's the schools 100th birthday! So all of Saturday activities can happen and we can celebrate our Villa Grove schools birthday with an open house on the 20th from 12 to 4.
Hopefully this is a good time for all of you.

#vgbluedevils #vgalumni

post_text:
This is an unprecedented time for all of us as this pandemic is impacting our families, our communities, and our way of life. Thank you for persevering through this difficult time. We are now all faced with the unique challenge of trying to provide academic and emotional support to our students while following the necessary guidelines of social distancing.

Mrs. Osborne has provided some good resources that guide how to spend quality time together and collectively improve family resilience during this time.

We wish you the best as we navigate this difficult time. We know that hope and human connection are both going to be vital ingredients to all of our collective resilience. Stay safe out there.

We will be sending out a survey later this week to check on our family‚Äôs needs.

Thanks for all you're doing!

#vgbluedevils #vgstayingconnected

Nothing to do today? Please take part in the 2020 Census! A kindergartner counted in the 2020 census this Spring will be starting high school when the next census comes around in 2030. That is 10 years of school supplies, teachers, school lunches, and so much more! This is your opportunity to help ensure they have a bright future.

Just completed mine and it took 9 minutes and 10 seconds to complete for a family of 5.

#4ourfuture #vgbluedevils

post_text:
This is what it‚Äôs all about!

Community members coming together to prepare snack packs for students during this time.

Not seen in these pictures:

Teachers/paraprofessionals working extra to prepare activities and lessons for students.

Custodians making sure every inch of our building is clean and safe.

Office staff answering phone calls and helping fix copiers from so many copies being made.

Administration spending their weekend making plans that will change before they are able to put them into action.

Cafeteria staff preparing extra meals, so students will not go hungry.

Parents scrambling to find daycare and preparing to be teachers for the next few weeks.

Together we will be stronger during these unprecedented times.

#vgbluedevils #ItTakesaVillage

Due to a confirmed case of Coronavirus in Champaign county Villa Grove schools will be closed Monday, March 16th. Teachers will report at 8:00 for a teacher institute day to prepare students at home learning packets. Students and/or family may come to the building between 10:00 am to 4:00 pm to pick up learning materials, chromebooks, and collect belongings. Please refer to our previous post for updates on student lunch options and other information. Again we thank you for your patience and understanding as we work through this unprecedented time. The situation is changing rapidly, and we will continue to provide updates as more information becomes available.

School Reach being sent out.
